payload.description: 2019 HackDuke Environmental Project: Website designed using nodeJS and React that inputs utility bills and compares values to national and state averages.

commits.message: Removed menu until database is implemented
testing git integration on new machine
changed some styling to condense intro a bit

issue.title: Add database
issue.body: Will allow us to store all 50 states' data, create user profiles + store user data, and give personalized advice rather than general advice about how to reduce energy expenditures.

comment.body: I will look into what is required to develop the database for React and where to find that data; personalized advice may be difficult to implement.

issue.title: Add more options for breakdowns of expenditures (i.e. gas, water, electric)
issue.body: For further down the road. Would provide a clearer picture of exactly what they're overspending on and what they should focus on cutting back on.

comment.body: That was the original plan for HackDuke, time constraints forced the project towards overall utilities.

issue.title: Add dropdown menu to choose state
issue.body: If users decide not to create an account, they can manually select their state since it won't be saved to a profile
